HEADWORD: Boudoir
<hw>Bou*doir"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr.
<ets>bouder</ets> to pout, be sulky.]</ety> <def>A small room, esp. if
pleasant, or elegantly furnished, to which a lady may retire to be
alone, or to receive intimate friends; a lady's bedroom; a lady's (or
sometimes a gentleman's) private room.</def>
<rj><au>Cowper.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

